    "privacy-section-5-content": "Where required, we collect, use, and disclose personal information with your consent, which may be express or implied depending on the circumstances and the sensitivity of the information.\n\nBy submitting your information to us, contacting us, booking a call, or continuing to use our website, you may be consenting to the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described in this Privacy Policy.\n\nYou may withdraw your consent, subject to legal or contractual restrictions and reasonable notice. Withdrawal of consent may affect our ability to provide certain services or respond to certain requests.",
    "privacy-section-6-title": "6. Cookies and Similar Technologies",
    "privacy-section-6-content": "Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to: keep the website functioning properly; understand how visitors use the site; improve performance and user experience; measure marketing and advertising effectiveness; support remarketing or ad targeting, where used.\n\nThese technologies may be provided by us or by third-party services such as analytics, advertising, scheduling, chat, or software platforms.\n\nYou can usually control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling some cookies may affect how the website functions.",
    "privacy-section-7-title": "7. Third-Party Tools and Service Providers",
    "privacy-section-7-content": "We may use third-party service providers and software platforms to help us operate our website, manage our business, and deliver our services. These may include providers for: website hosting; analytics; calendars and scheduling; forms and lead capture; SaaS platforms used to deliver, manage, and support our services; email communications; payment processing; cloud storage; chatbot, voice, automation, or AI-related functionality; customer support and internal operations.\n\nThese providers may process personal information on our behalf or, in some cases, under their own terms and privacy policies, depending on how the service is used.\n\nWe require service providers to handle personal information in a manner appropriate to the sensitivity of the information and the services they provide.",
    "privacy-section-8-title": "8. AI and Automated Tools",
    "privacy-section-8-content": "Because our business may use AI-enabled tools, automations, chat systems, voice systems, and workflow tools, personal information may sometimes be processed through these systems in order to deliver services, respond to inquiries, support operations, or generate outputs.\n\nWhere such tools are used: outputs may not always be accurate or complete; personal information should not be submitted unless reasonably necessary; human review may be used where appropriate; third-party technology providers may be involved in processing data.\n\nWe do not intentionally use personal information for unrelated purposes without appropriate authorization or legal basis.",
    "privacy-section-9-title": "9. When We May Disclose Personal Information",
    "privacy-section-9-content": "We may disclose personal information: to service providers helping us operate our business or website; to payment processors or invoicing platforms where needed; to professional advisors such as accountants, lawyers, insurers, or auditors; where required by law, regulation, court order, subpoena, or lawful authority; to protect our rights, safety, systems, property, or legal interests; in connection with a business transaction such as a merger, financing, acquisition, reorganization, or sale of assets; with your consent or at your direction.\n\nWe do not sell your personal information in the ordinary meaning of that term unless clearly disclosed and legally permitted.",
    "privacy-section-10-title": "10. Cross-Border Processing",
    "privacy-section-10-content": "Some of our service providers may store or process personal information outside Québec or outside Canada, including in the United States or other jurisdictions.\n\nWhen information is processed outside your jurisdiction, it may be subject to the laws of that other jurisdiction and may be accessible to courts, governments, regulators, or law enforcement in accordance with those laws.",
    "privacy-section-11-title": "11. Retention",
    "privacy-section-11-content": "We retain personal information only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, or as required or permitted by law.\n\nRetention periods may depend on factors such as: the nature of the information; the purpose for which it was collected; legal, accounting, tax, insurance, or regulatory requirements; dispute resolution and enforcement needs.\n\nWhen personal information is no longer required, we will delete it, anonymize it, or securely destroy it, as appropriate.",
    "privacy-section-12-title": "12. Safeguards",
    "privacy-section-12-content": "We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect personal information against loss, theft, unauthorized access, disclosure, copying, use, or modification.\n\nHowever, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is completely secure. As a result, we cannot guarantee absolute security.",
    "privacy-section-13-title": "13. Your Rights",
    "privacy-section-13-content": "Depending on the laws that apply, you may have rights regarding your personal information, including the right to: request access to personal information we hold about you; request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal information; withdraw consent in certain circumstances; request information about how your personal information is used; make a complaint about our privacy practices.\n\nTo exercise any of these rights, contact us using the information in this policy. We may need to verify your identity before responding.",
    "privacy-section-14-title": "14. Marketing Communications",
    "privacy-section-14-content": "If you receive marketing emails from us, you can unsubscribe at any time using the unsubscribe link in the message or by contacting us directly.\n\nEven if you unsubscribe from marketing messages, we may still send you service-related or transactional communications where necessary.",
    "privacy-section-15-title": "15. Children's Privacy",
